187.2	Death	Death	Death is the term used to describe the cessation of all biological functions that sustain a living organism. Phenomena which commonly bring about death include old age, predation, malnutrition, disease, and accidents or trauma resulting in terminal injury. All known organisms inevitably experience death. Bodies of living organisms begin to decompose shortly after death.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Skullclose.jpg/250px-Skullclose.jpg
